eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.immutable

Class ImmutableListWrapper<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.immutable.AbstractImmutableCollectionWrapper<T>
      • eu.excitement.entailment.core.utilities.immutable.ImmutableListWrapper<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ImmutableCollection<T>, ImmutableList<T>, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<T>

    public class ImmutableListWrapper<T>
extends AbstractImmutableCollectionWrapper<T>
implements ImmutableList<T>
    Simple implementation of ImmutableList. It gets a java.util.List in its constructor, and exposes only "read" operations on that list.

    Note that the underlying list is the same list supplied in the constructor, and therefore, if the list is changed by another code that holds a reference to that list, the ImmutableList is changed as well. This implementation only insures that the code that holds the ImmutableList cannot change it.

    Author:
    Asher Stern
